</nav>

<!-- HERO -->
<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <span class="label label-dark">Platform Features</span>
    <h1>THE CONTINUITY LAYER THAT<br>SOLVES N×M INTEGRATION</h1>
    <p class="sub">Connect N tools to one Capability Fabric. Connect M AI models to the same fabric. Result: N + M connections, not N × M. Own the memory. Switch AI anytime.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- N+M EQUATION VISUAL -->
<section class="bento-section">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="equation">
      <span class="equation-term">N TOOLS</span>
      <span class="equation-operator">×</span>
      <span class="equation-term">M AI MODELS</span>
      <span class="equation-operator">=</span>
      <span class="equation-term equation-bad">N × M</span>
      <span class="equation-vs">vs</span>
      <span class="equation-term">N TOOLS</span>
      <span class="equation-operator">+</span>
      <span class="equation-term">M AI MODELS</span>
      <span class="equation-operator">=</span>
      <span class="equation-result">N + M</span>
    </div>

    <!-- BENTO GRID -->
    <div class="bento-grid">
      <!-- Card 1: Core Problem -->
      <div class="bento-card span-2 dark">
        <div class="bento-num">The Problem</div>
        <div class="bento-title">THE N×M INTEGRATION EXPLOSION</div>
        <div class="bento-desc">Every tool talks to every AI. Every AI needs every tool. 10 tools × 5 AI models = 50 integration points. Each breaks independently. Each requires separate memory.</div>
        <div class="diagram">
          <div class="diagram-flow">
            <div class="diagram-node">HubSpot</div>
            <div class="diagram-node">Jira</div>
            <div class="diagram-node">Slack</div>
          </div>
          <div style="text-align:center;padding:0.5rem 0;font-family:'IBM Plex Mono';font-size:0.6rem;color:var(--gold-pale)">↓ × ↓ × ↓</div>
          <div class="diagram-flow">
            <div class="diagram-node">Claude</div>
            <div class="diagram-node">GPT</div>
            <div class="diagram-node">Gemini</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 2: Solution -->
      <div class="bento-card span-2 accent">
        <div class="bento-num">The Solution</div>
        <div class="bento-title">ONE CAPABILITY FABRIC</div>
        <div class="bento-desc">Tools connect once to the Spine. AI models connect once to the Spine. Memory stays in the fabric. Switch models in a day, not six months.</div>
        <div class="diagram">
          <div class="diagram-flow">
            <div class="diagram-node">All Tools</div>
            <div class="diagram-arrow">→</div>
            <div class="diagram-node highlight">THE SPINE</div>
            <div class="diagram-arrow">←</div>
            <div class="diagram-node">All AI</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

<!-- FEATURE 1: MCP-Native Architecture DEEP DIVE -->
<section class="feature-deep">
  <div class="wrap-md">
    <div class="fd-grid">
      <div class="fd-content">
        <div class="fd-num">01 · Architecture</div>
        <h2>MCP-NATIVE ARCHITECTURE</h2>
        <p class="lead">Built from first principles on the Model Context Protocol. Every connection, every capability, every memory operation speaks MCP natively — no translation layers, no adapters, no protocol debt.</p>
        <ul class="fd-list">
          <li>Native MCP transport from first byte to last</li>
          <li>OAuth 2.0 with RS256 JWTs for every client</li>
          <li>18 canonical tools: memory.*, spine.*, signal.*, proposal.*, search.*</li>
          <li>Any MCP-compatible AI client connects in minutes</li>
          <li>Service bindings for zero-latency inter-worker communication</li>
          <li>Discovery endpoint for automatic client configuration</li>
          <li>Grant types: authorization_code, client_credentials, refresh_token</li>
          <li>Scope enforcement: per-tool filtering and tenant isolation</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="fd-mock">
        <div style="margin-bottom:1rem">
          <span class="mock-badge">MCP Protocol</span>
        </div>
        <div style="font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:0.6rem;color:var(--paper)">
          <div style="color:rgba(244,240,232,0.5)">// OAuth Discovery</div>
          <div>GET /.well-known/oauth-authorization-server</div>
          <div style="margin-top:1rem;color:rgba(244,240,232,0.5)">// Token Request</div>
          <div>POST /oauth/token</div>
          <div style="color:var(--gold);margin-left:1rem">→ RS256 JWT (1hr TTL)</div>
          <div style="margin-top:1rem;color:rgba(244,240,232,0.5)">// MCP Call</div>
          <div>POST /mcp</div>
          <div style="margin-left:1rem;color:rgba(244,240,232,0.7)">{ "tool": "memory.read",</div>
          <div style="margin-left:1.5rem;color:rgba(244,240,232,0.7)">"tenant_id": "...",</div>
          <div style="margin-left:1.5rem;color:rgba(244,240,232,0.7)">"session_id": "..." }</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FEATURE 2: Capability Fabric DEEP DIVE -->
<section class="feature-deep alt">
  <div class="wrap-md">
    <div class="fd-grid">
      <div class="fd-content">
        <div class="fd-num">02 · Core Engine</div>
        <h2>CAPABILITY FABRIC — THE SPINE</h2>
        <p class="lead">The Spine is the canonical entity resolution substrate. One Person exists once — across HubSpot, Jira, Gmail, Salesforce, and every tool you connect. Relationships, traits, and signals are resolved once and compounded forever.</p>
        <ul class="fd-list">
          <li>Entity Resolution: one entity across all connected systems</li>
          <li>18 core traits + 7 canonical resource types</li>
          <li>Relationship graph that exists nowhere else in your stack</li>
          <li>Signal layer: change → think → approve → act → loop</li>
          <li>Eight-stage cognitive normalization pipeline</li>
          <li>LLM-in-the-loop at stages 2, 3, 4, 6 for intelligence</li>
          <li>Normalization paid once per entity — compounding begins immediately</li>
          <li>Object identity by nature, not label (Contact = Lead = Reporter = Person)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="fd-mock">
        <div style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:1rem">
          <span style="font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:0.55rem;color:rgba(244,240,232,0.5);letter-spacing:0.1em">ENTITY RESOLUTION</span>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.5rem">
          <div class="mock-card"><div class="mock-card-title">HubSpot Contact</div><div style="font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:0.6rem;color:var(--paper)">john@acme.com</div></div>
          <div class="mock-card"><div class="mock-card-title">Salesforce Lead</div><div style="font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:0.6rem;color:var(--paper)">john@acme.com</div></div>
          <div class="mock-card"><div class="mock-card-title">Jira Reporter</div><div style="font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:0.6rem;color:var(--paper)">john@acme.com</div></div>
        </div>
        <div style="text-align:center;margin:1rem 0">
          <span style="font-size:1.5rem;color:var(--gold)">↓</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mock-card" style="background:rgba(184,148,63,0.2);border:1px solid var(--gold)">
          <div class="mock-card-title" style="color:var(--gold)">Spine Entity</div>
          <div style="font-family:'Bebas Neue',sans-serif;font-size:1.2rem;color:var(--paper)">John Smith</div>
          <div style="font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:0.5rem;color:rgba(244,240,232,0.7)">Person · 3 sources · 12 relationships</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

      <!-- Card 3: MCP Native -->
      <div class="bento-card">
