            <div style="font-size:0.5rem;color:var(--slate);margin-top:0.25rem">Contact promoted...</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

<!-- FEATURE 3: Memory Loop DEEP DIVE -->
<section class="feature-deep">
  <div class="wrap-md">
    <div class="fd-grid">
      <div class="fd-content">
        <div class="fd-num">03 · Memory</div>
        <h2>THE MEMORY LOOP</h2>
        <p class="lead">Conversational context becomes institutional knowledge. Three memory tiers — conversational, organizational, and personal — governed by humans and owned by your organization. Switch AI models and pick up exactly where you left off.</p>
        <ul class="fd-list">
          <li>Conversational memory: session-scoped, role-tagged (user/assistant/system)</li>
          <li>Organizational memory: promoted, governed, immutable once approved</li>
          <li>Personal memory: behavioral patterns, preferences, decisions per user</li>
          <li>pgvector similarity search across all memory tiers</li>
          <li>Memory persists across AI model switches — no context loss</li>
          <li>Dual-write synchronization: edge cache + fortress database</li>
          <li>Governance state machine: draft → pending → approved → published</li>
          <li>30-day, 1-year, or unlimited retention based on tier</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="fd-mock">
        <div style="font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:0.55rem;margin-bottom:1rem">
          <span style="color:rgba(244,240,232,0.5)">MEMORY TIERS</span>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.75rem">
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.75rem">
            <div style="width:10px;height:10px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--gold)"></div>
            <div style="flex:1">
              <div style="font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:0.55rem;color:rgba(244,240,232,0.5)">CONVERSATIONAL</div>
              <div style="font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--paper)">Session context, chat history</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div style="margin-left:5px;border-left:1px dashed rgba(244,240,232,0.2);height:20px"></div>
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.75rem">
            <div style="width:10px;height:10px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--gold)"></div>
            <div style="flex:1">
              <div style="font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:0.55rem;color:rgba(244,240,232,0.5)">ORGANIZATIONAL</div>
              <div style="font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--paper)">Governed institutional knowledge</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div style="margin-left:5px;border-left:1px dashed rgba(244,240,232,0.2);height:20px"></div>
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.75rem">
            <div style="width:10px;height:10px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--gold)"></div>
            <div style="flex:1">
              <div style="font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:0.55rem;color:rgba(244,240,232,0.5)">PERSONAL</div>
              <div style="font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--paper)">User preferences & patterns</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top:1.5rem;padding:0.75rem;background:rgba(184,148,63,0.15);border-radius:4px;border:1px solid rgba(184,148,63,0.3)">
          <div style="font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:0.5rem;color:var(--gold)">PGVECTOR SIMILARITY</div>
          <div style="font-size:0.65rem;color:var(--paper);margin-top:0.25rem">Semantic search across all tiers</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FEATURE 4: Multi-AI Orchestration DEEP DIVE -->
<section class="feature-deep alt">
  <div class="wrap-md">
    <div class="fd-grid">
      <div class="fd-content">
        <div class="fd-num">04 · Orchestration</div>
        <h2>MULTI-AI ORCHESTRATION</h2>
        <p class="lead">Authorize Claude, ChatGPT, Gemini, Perplexity, local LLMs, or any MCP-compatible AI as clients of your Capability Fabric. One integration surface. Unlimited AI consumers. Zero vendor lock-in.</p>
        <ul class="fd-list">
          <li>Any AI connects via standard OAuth 2.0 authorization</li>
          <li>Tenant-isolated, scope-enforced access per AI client</li>
          <li>Switch AI models in 1 day instead of 6 months</li>
          <li>Context transfer: memory follows the conversation, not the vendor</li>
          <li>Parallel AI evaluation: same capability, different models</li>
          <li>Graceful degradation: if one AI goes down, others continue</li>
          <li>No rebuilding integrations when you change AI providers</li>
          <li>Run evaluations across models with identical context</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="fd-mock">
        <div style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:1.5rem">
          <span style="font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:0.55rem;color:rgba(244,240,232,0.5);letter-spacing:0.1em">AI CLIENTS → CAPABILITY FABRIC</span>
        </div>
        <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:0.5rem;margin-bottom:1rem">
          <div class="mock-node"><span class="dot"></span>Claude</div>
          <div class="mock-node"><span class="dot"></span>ChatGPT</div>
